 Master Smith

 Santa Barbara (California), Jan. 29 (AP): Rapper-turned-Oscar nominee Will Smith was honoured with a master of his craft award at the Santa Barbara International Film Festival.

 Smith is nominated for a best-actor Oscar for his performance in The Pursuit of Happyness as a struggling single father in San Francisco who beats the odds and goes from rags to riches.

 Asked what it takes to be a good father, Smith said patience, compassion and commitment. Hes the father of three in real life, including 7-year-old Jaden, who co-stars in the movie. 

 Youve got to really want to be a good father, he said on the red carpet outside the Arlington Theatre on Saturday night. 

 Tom Cruise presented the festivals Modern Master Award to Smith. Cruise, Smith and wife Jada Pinkett Smith then posed for pictures. Smith said he was pleased with the films success. People are enjoying the film and its reached a level of critical acclaim; it cant get any better than this. 




